Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Halve @red bell pepper{1} and @yellow bell pepper{1} lengthwise. Remove core, seeds, and white ribs. Rub with a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place on a #baking sheet{} cut-side down. Roast in oven until soft, about ~{20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, bring 1 1/2 cups water and @veggie stock concentrate{1%cube} to boil in a #small pot{}. Once boiling, add @golden grain blend{1%cup}. Lower heat and reduce to a simmer. Cover and cook until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. Remove from heat and keep covered.

Halve, peel, and dice @shallot{1}. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Finely chop @sun-dried tomatoes{1.5%oz}. Chop @zucchini{1} into ½-inch pieces. Cut @fresh mozzarella{4%oz} into small cubes. Finely chop @parsley{1/4%oz}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add shallot and sun-dried tomatoes. Cook, tossing, until shallots are softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer mixture to a #large bowl{}.

Increase heat to high and heat another drizzle of oil in same pan. Add zucchini. Season with salt, pepper, and @herbes de Provence{1%tbsp}. Cook, tossing, until soft and lightly charred, ~{5-7%minutes}. Add to #bowl{} with sun-dried tomato mixture. Toss to combine. Fluff golden grain blend with a #fork{}, then add to bowl along with mozzarella and toss. Season with salt and pepper.

Flip bell peppers over and fill with as much stuffing as will fit. Return baking sheet to oven and bake until mozzarella melts, ~{3-5%minutes}. Stir parsley into remaining stuffing, then divide mixture between plates. Top with stuffed pepper halves.